&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a substantive post which has become available following the recent retirement of a long serving Associate Specialist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will work across the South and West Localites, our two community mental health teams primarily working out of the Redhill Clinic (main offices based at Springwell Centre).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will have experience with the full spectrum of psychiatric morbidity. This post is based in a multidisciplinary setting and the post holder will work closely with all the members of the team (CPNs, Psychologists, Social Workers &amp; Graduate Mental Health Workers). There will also be the experience of conducting home visits.The care delivered is recovery-focused, placing emphasis on individuals’ strengths and goals for the future.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;*Strictly no agencies please&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Gil Kovac, Consultant Psychiatrist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;gil.kovac@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
